1
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:22,940
♪Only after bloom comes fruit♪

2
00:00:24,350 --> 00:00:28,320
♪Who says glory must fade to the past♪

3
00:00:30,980 --> 00:00:36,070
♪Only through thunder
do you reach the clouds♪

4
00:00:37,270 --> 00:00:42,180
♪Who made you the crown of every peak♪

5
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:46,990
♪I stand at the center of the stage♪

6
00:00:46,990 --> 00:00:50,060
♪My shadow is pinned against the wall♪

7
00:00:50,770 --> 00:00:55,720
♪Facing the light earns every medal♪

8
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:59,940
♪Little birds,
save your needless pecking♪

9
00:00:59,940 --> 00:01:03,220
♪The open sky rises high♪

10
00:01:03,760 --> 00:01:08,890
♪When night falls,
the moon begins to shine♪

11
00:01:09,660 --> 00:01:12,920
♪I stand in the heart of these lands♪

12
00:01:12,920 --> 00:01:16,280
♪My shadow bears no crown or robe♪

13
00:01:16,690 --> 00:01:22,360
♪Then I know truth needs no disguise♪

14
00:01:22,770 --> 00:01:26,020
♪The green hills see me as I am♪

15
00:01:26,020 --> 00:01:29,350
♪Like dew, lightning,
and moon on the river♪

16
00:01:29,750 --> 00:01:33,790
♪Showing me exactly who I am♪

17
00:01:33,790 --> 00:01:35,040
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 37=

19
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:18,640
So, this is where you herded sheep.

20
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:19,480
Yes.

21
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:25,320
It's beautiful here.

22
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:28,360
Just like you.

23
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:32,080
Your name is beautiful too.

24
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:35,280
I only found out lately

25
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:37,640
that your name comes from an old poem

26
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:40,840
by Li Bai of the Tang Dynasty.

27
00:02:41,920 --> 00:02:42,840
You know,

28
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:44,880
when I was a kid,

29
00:02:44,880 --> 00:02:47,520
I was awful at memorizing texts,

30
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:48,800
especially poems and stuff.

31
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:51,200
But I loved this poem

32
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:53,960
after one read.

33
00:02:54,480 --> 00:02:55,320
Really.

34
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:58,880
When I read it,

35
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:01,920
I felt something I can't explain.

36
00:03:04,880 --> 00:03:06,000
Yi Qin'e.

37
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:09,040
The flute sobs.

38
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:13,200
Qin'e wakes up, only to see the moon
over Qin Tower.

39
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:15,760
The moon over Qin Tower

40
00:03:16,730 --> 00:03:18,200
and the green willows year after year

41
00:03:18,890 --> 00:03:20,690
bear witness to the parting
on Baling Bridge.

42
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:25,680
On Leyou Plain, crisp autumn falls.

43
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:28,240
On the ancient road to Xianyang,

44
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:31,680
there's no more word for her.

45
00:03:33,320 --> 00:03:34,600
No more word for her.

46
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:38,800
The west wind and fading light

47
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:42,080
bring out the Han ruins.

48
00:03:56,040 --> 00:03:56,940
Look, there it is.

49
00:03:56,940 --> 00:03:57,780
It came out there.

50
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:10,000
No more word for her.

51
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:13,720
The west wind and fading light

52
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:17,760
bring out the Han ruins.

53
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:26,040
So beautiful.

54
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:38,480
You're awake.

55
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:39,840
Why not sleep a bit longer?

56
00:04:40,160 --> 00:04:42,400
I'm up. We said we'd head back today.

57
00:04:43,960 --> 00:04:44,920
Where's Liu Hongbing?

58
00:04:45,320 --> 00:04:46,240
Your boyfriend

59
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:48,680
drove Cungen out early this morning.

60
00:04:55,960 --> 00:04:56,800
Laidi,

61
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:59,200
Mom told me everything last night.

62
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:00,800
Come on.

63
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:02,640
After all this fuss,

64
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:04,560
don't get upset.

65
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,920
And don't think I don't care.

66
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:08,600
Honestly,

67
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:10,720
I'd want to trade places with you.

68
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:13,120
If I were in your shoes now,

69
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:14,520
they could say anything they want.

70
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:17,000
If you were here in these hills,

71
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,320
you'd have it even harder

72
00:05:19,280 --> 00:05:20,960
than now after just a few days.

73
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:24,120
I just want to sing opera.

74
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:27,760
Don't I want a good life? Can I?

75
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:31,080
Look around these villages.

76
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:34,080
Everyone fights to make some money.

77
00:05:34,280 --> 00:05:36,120
Everyone struggles

78
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:37,560
to raise a child.

79
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:39,000
Everyone has their struggles.

80
00:05:39,880 --> 00:05:42,280
At least you're doing what you love.

81
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:43,400
Be grateful.

82
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:45,160
Go back and do what you need to do.

83
00:05:48,320 --> 00:05:49,560
Uncle, Aunt.

84
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:50,520
We're back.

85
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:52,520
We bought you a few things.

86
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:54,600
Why buy anything?

87
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:55,680
You shouldn't have.

88
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:57,160
We came

89
00:05:57,160 --> 00:05:58,040
in such a hurry.

90
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:59,760
It wasn't proper. Look.

91
00:05:59,760 --> 00:06:00,600
Share these things

92
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:02,080
with the relatives.

93
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:03,800
What kind of liquor do you like?

94
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:05,880
We don't know about types.

95
00:06:05,880 --> 00:06:07,400
We're not picky about that.

96
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:09,400
Look at you, being so fancy.

97
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:10,920
You knew we had a trip ahead,

98
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:12,080
yet you're still wasting time.

99
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:13,960
I just filled the tank in town.

100
00:06:13,960 --> 00:06:15,120
Once we head for Chang'an,

101
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:16,080
we won't need to stop.

102
00:06:16,880 --> 00:06:18,160
Good prep saves time later.

103
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:20,240
- Right.
- Wufu, hurry up.

104
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:21,240
I'm not done yet.

105
00:06:21,760 --> 00:06:23,560
Hongbing, we got Laidi
some herbal medicine.

106
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:24,800
We don't have much else here.

107
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:26,200
Take it back and brew it for her

108
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:27,120
to soothe her throat.

109
00:06:28,280 --> 00:06:29,380
All right. Thanks, sis.

110
00:06:29,390 --> 00:06:30,780
- Thanks, bro.
- Don't mention it.

111
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:31,640
Qin'e.

112
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:32,920
Pack up. We're leaving. Hurry.

113
00:06:37,320 --> 00:06:38,600
Once you get back,

114
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:40,000
hurry up and get married.

115
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,640
You're not getting any younger.

116
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:44,240
Your dad and I want grandkids.

117
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:46,320
Hongbing's parents

118
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:47,440
must be eager too.

119
00:06:47,960 --> 00:06:49,720
Aunt, don't worry.

120
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:51,080
I'll handle this.

121
00:06:51,780 --> 00:06:52,670
Right, right.

122
00:06:52,670 --> 00:06:53,720
Let's go, hurry up.

123
00:06:54,160 --> 00:06:55,520
We need to be back before dark.

124
00:06:55,880 --> 00:06:57,000
Look out for each other.

125
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:57,860
Goodbye.

126
00:06:57,860 --> 00:06:58,720
Take it easy.

127
00:06:58,720 --> 00:06:59,560
Bye-bye.

128
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:03,220
Hey, kid.

129
00:07:03,220 --> 00:07:04,060
Listen to me.

130
00:07:04,060 --> 00:07:04,980
Study hard, okay?

131
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:07,440
After graduation, find me in Chang'an.

132
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:08,600
Okay, okay.

133
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:13,240
That's good.

134
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:14,200
Good kid.

135
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:27,480
Hongbing,

136
00:07:27,960 --> 00:07:29,080
where have you been?

137
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:30,880
A tiger's den?

138
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:32,400
So what?

139
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:34,710
My lifetime happiness is at stake.

140
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,120
I'd go anywhere if I had to.

141
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:41,580
Are you done with that woman

142
00:07:41,590 --> 00:07:43,000
from the provincial troupe for good?

143
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:45,280
What's it to you?

144
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:46,680
Rumors are everywhere.

145
00:07:47,080 --> 00:07:47,920
What rumors?

146
00:07:57,080 --> 00:07:58,040
No surprise.

147
00:07:58,360 --> 00:08:00,360
Those trashy magazines are everywhere.

148
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:03,360
What star hasn't had rumors?

149
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:05,960
It's just sour grapes.

150
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:08,240
Do you know who started the rumor?

151
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:09,640
How would I know?

152
00:08:09,840 --> 00:08:10,960
If I knew, I'd make him pay.

153
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,040
Hongbing,

154
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:13,600
I have a buddy.

155
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:15,800
He's well-connected on Wenyi Road.

156
00:08:16,060 --> 00:08:17,100
How about I introduce you?

157
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:18,820
Sure.

158
00:08:18,820 --> 00:08:20,940
(Yi Qin'e's Romantic Past)

159
00:08:25,620 --> 00:08:26,510
What are you doing?

160
00:08:26,510 --> 00:08:27,380
I'm washing the car.

161
00:08:27,380 --> 00:08:28,440
What? Can't you see?

162
00:08:28,440 --> 00:08:29,920
Why spray here?

163
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:31,420
Move. What are you staring at?

164
00:08:31,420 --> 00:08:32,260
Go on.

165
00:08:32,260 --> 00:08:33,120
Move, move. Hurry up.

166
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:34,640
You're rotten to the core.

167
00:08:34,640 --> 00:08:35,520
I'm telling you.

168
00:08:35,520 --> 00:08:36,760
Don't you dare stare.

169
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:39,840
Caixiang, this garlic won't do.

170
00:08:40,160 --> 00:08:41,760
I'll get you some good ones later.

171
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:44,320
I know a guy who deals in garlic.

172
00:08:44,760 --> 00:08:46,920
I'll get you big solo garlic.

173
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:48,620
(Hua Ting Xiang Hui)
With that in liangpi,

174
00:08:48,640 --> 00:08:49,680
it tastes amazing.

175
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:52,520
You're stuck here all day now?

176
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:53,440
I'm peeling garlic.

177
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:56,440
You like liangpi more than I do?

178
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:59,340
- ♪I truly fear♪
- Caixiang makes it so tasty.

179
00:08:59,340 --> 00:09:04,000
- ♪What if the Wen family knows♪
- So dramatic.

180
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:08,410
- ♪I can't rest easy♪
- How's Laidi been?

181
00:09:08,410 --> 00:09:12,760
- ♪I look around♪
- Fine. She's practicing.

182
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:14,720
She seems the same as before.

183
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:18,040
- ♪No one's around♪
- Maybe it's over.

184
00:09:18,570 --> 00:09:22,200
- ♪I step up and kneel♪
- Some wounds hide.

185
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:30,380
♪I keep calling for you♪

186
00:09:31,180 --> 00:09:35,100
(Qinchuan Province
Qinqiang Opera Theater)

187
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:05,320
Come on. Let's start.

188
00:10:08,080 --> 00:10:09,200
Morning, Master Chen.

189
00:10:17,120 --> 00:10:21,680
♪To the residence in Chang'an♪

190
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:27,760
♪I, the fox maid, must leave alone♪

191
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:31,240
♪I can hardly leave my loved ones♪

192
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:34,360
♪I can hardly leave
this fleeting warmth♪

193
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:38,680
♪I can't bear my family's harsh torment♪

194
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:41,360
♪I can't bear the immortals closing in♪

195
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:44,840
♪I can't bear the rules
that are as sharp as needles♪

196
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:50,720
♪Enough, I'll harden my heart♪

197
00:10:50,880 --> 00:10:56,800
♪Leap off the cliff,
and sever love's root♪

198
00:11:08,180 --> 00:11:09,040
Sorry.

199
00:11:09,040 --> 00:11:10,000
I spaced out.

200
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:11,040
Let's do it again.

201
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:21,240
Wash or cut?

202
00:11:21,560 --> 00:11:22,540
I'm looking for someone.

203
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:29,840
Laohei.

204
00:11:33,040 --> 00:11:33,960
Just a small token.

205
00:11:34,640 --> 00:11:35,640
Please accept it.

206
00:11:38,760 --> 00:11:39,840
I'm Qin'e's boyfriend.

207
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:41,960
You?

208
00:11:42,680 --> 00:11:44,400
You're Yi Qin'e's boyfriend?

209
00:11:46,700 --> 00:11:47,860
Do you know she has an uncle?

210
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:48,920
Of course.

211
00:11:49,160 --> 00:11:50,000
Hu Sanyuan, right?

212
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:51,560
And an aunt.

213
00:11:51,760 --> 00:11:53,000
Hua Caixiang.

214
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:55,960
So, it's true.

215
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:59,000
It seems

216
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:01,000
you know her uncle well.

217
00:12:01,560 --> 00:12:02,720
I'm not close to her uncle.

218
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:04,280
I know Caixiang well.

219
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:06,400
What is it? Tell me.

220
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:09,000
Help me find someone.

221
00:12:09,760 --> 00:12:10,600
Who?

222
00:12:10,680 --> 00:12:12,840
Wang Qinsheng, who used to be
in the provincial troupe.

223
00:12:13,720 --> 00:12:14,960
The Xiaosheng?

224
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:17,280
The one who partnered with Yi Qin'e?

225
00:12:17,880 --> 00:12:18,720
That's him.

226
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:20,360
Why look for him?

227
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:22,070
Hey.

228
00:12:22,070 --> 00:12:23,440
What took you so long?

229
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:25,320
I've been swamped lately.

230
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:26,880
The troupe's staging a big show.

231
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:28,520
I'm the lead.

232
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:29,760
The troupe can't be

233
00:12:29,760 --> 00:12:31,080
without me.

234
00:12:31,550 --> 00:12:32,700
How many are in your family?

235
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:33,680
Four...

236
00:12:35,520 --> 00:12:36,360
Who is it?

237
00:12:37,040 --> 00:12:37,880
Who?

238
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:39,320
What are you doing?

239
00:12:45,680 --> 00:12:46,640
Liu Hongbing.

240
00:12:47,020 --> 00:12:48,470
(Xiaoli Massage)
What are you doing?

241
00:12:48,740 --> 00:12:49,600
Why take photos?

242
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:51,000
Come here, give me the film.

243
00:12:51,920 --> 00:12:52,920
I'll give it to you.

244
00:12:52,920 --> 00:12:53,780
Come on.

245
00:12:53,780 --> 00:12:54,640
Give it a try.

246
00:12:54,640 --> 00:12:56,280
Hey, what do you want?

247
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:57,840
What do I want?

248
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,280
I want to send a copy

249
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:01,200
of this photo to your workplace

250
00:13:01,920 --> 00:13:03,760
and Tangcheng Tales,

251
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:05,880
so you can experience

252
00:13:05,880 --> 00:13:07,200
what it feels like to be famous.

253
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:08,840
Hongbing,

254
00:13:09,520 --> 00:13:10,360
tell me.

255
00:13:10,680 --> 00:13:12,040
How did I ever offend you?

256
00:13:12,760 --> 00:13:14,280
You spread rumors about Qin'e.

257
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:15,800
What a wimp.

258
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,560
You messed with the wrong person.

259
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:19,300
I'm not that kind of person.

260
00:13:19,300 --> 00:13:20,160
I wouldn't do that.

261
00:13:20,160 --> 00:13:21,360
That'd be way too humiliating.

262
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:22,440
Keep pretending.

263
00:13:23,040 --> 00:13:23,920
Go on, keep acting.

264
00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:25,000
Come on.

265
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:26,090
- Act.
- I swear.

266
00:13:26,760 --> 00:13:27,800
If I started that rumor,

267
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:29,160
I'd be an extra forever

268
00:13:29,160 --> 00:13:30,240
and lose all my family.

269
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,120
Was it this guy?

270
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:35,920
Was it him?

271
00:13:35,930 --> 00:13:37,160
- It must be him!
- Master Hu.

272
00:13:37,160 --> 00:13:38,000
Uncle! Uncle!

273
00:13:38,140 --> 00:13:39,000
It wasn't him.

274
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,760
Uncle! Uncle!

275
00:13:41,040 --> 00:13:42,360
It really wasn't. Probably not.

276
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:43,420
- I didn't do it.
- Uncle!

277
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:44,400
Don't be mad.

278
00:13:44,640 --> 00:13:46,360
I have to sing opera, Uncle.

279
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:48,000
Uncle, really...

280
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:49,160
Really...

281
00:13:55,880 --> 00:13:56,720
I'm sorry.

282
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:05,360
Maybe it wasn't that guy after all.

283
00:14:06,640 --> 00:14:07,960
There were a lot of things

284
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:10,440
about Qin'e at County Troupe.

285
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:12,840
Wang Qinsheng couldn't know that.

286
00:14:16,720 --> 00:14:17,600
Uncle, do you think

287
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:19,040
Chu Jiahe could've done this?

288
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:21,520
The more I think about it...

289
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:22,960
Stop thinking about it.

290
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:26,440
Don't stir things up
before you find proof.

291
00:14:26,920 --> 00:14:29,040
If you keep digging,

292
00:14:30,120 --> 00:14:31,320
you'll never get past it.

293
00:14:34,120 --> 00:14:35,600
Let it go, starting now.

294
00:14:36,880 --> 00:14:38,160
Don't bring it up again.

295
00:14:39,240 --> 00:14:41,160
I saw you with Laohei earlier.

296
00:14:42,080 --> 00:14:43,130
How much did you give him?

297
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:44,160
He wouldn't take it.

298
00:14:44,880 --> 00:14:45,960
He did it for my sake.

299
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:49,120
At least he's got a conscience.

300
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:49,960
He said

301
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:51,800
that it was for Aunt Hua.

302
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:54,360
That clueless fool.

303
00:14:54,960 --> 00:14:56,320
Uncle, don't be mad.

304
00:14:57,720 --> 00:14:59,000
He can't compare to you.

305
00:14:59,000 --> 00:14:59,840
Not even close.

306
00:15:02,240 --> 00:15:03,680
Right. Enough about me.

307
00:15:04,520 --> 00:15:06,120
How are things with Qin'e now?

308
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:08,200
Nothing new.

309
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:09,640
Same as before.

310
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:11,920
You're not getting any younger.

311
00:15:12,880 --> 00:15:14,840
Qin'e's career is stable now.

312
00:15:15,360 --> 00:15:17,320
Some things should be planned.

313
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:21,960
Uncle, do you approve?

314
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:24,520
What good is my approval?

315
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:26,880
All across Chang'an,

316
00:15:26,880 --> 00:15:29,000
everyone knows you're Yi Qin'e's family.

317
00:15:31,080 --> 00:15:33,360
But Qin'e hasn't said yes yet.

318
00:15:33,880 --> 00:15:35,080
Then I can't help you.

319
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:40,520
What do women even think?

320
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:45,560
Didn't you say

321
00:15:45,560 --> 00:15:46,560
there's no trick in love

322
00:15:46,560 --> 00:15:48,000
but a true heart

323
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:49,560
that you have to show?

324
00:15:49,960 --> 00:15:50,800
Exactly.

325
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:55,640
Uncle, if you ask me,

326
00:15:56,120 --> 00:15:57,520
you and Aunt Hua

327
00:15:57,520 --> 00:15:58,920
are messier than Qin'e and me.

328
00:15:59,880 --> 00:16:01,120
Between you two,

329
00:16:01,120 --> 00:16:02,160
there's a third person.

330
00:16:02,760 --> 00:16:04,640
Get lost. You never say anything nice.

331
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:19,960
Qin'e, open up! Qin'e!

332
00:16:19,960 --> 00:16:20,800
It's me.

333
00:16:24,260 --> 00:16:25,150
Qin'e.

334
00:16:25,150 --> 00:16:26,000
What?

335
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:27,360
Look here.

336
00:16:27,640 --> 00:16:28,600
What are you holding?

337
00:16:28,920 --> 00:16:30,200
A camcorder.

338
00:16:30,520 --> 00:16:31,360
Come on, hurry.

339
00:16:32,920 --> 00:16:35,160
I barely got this from a friend.

340
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:36,640
You've been down lately, right?

341
00:16:37,640 --> 00:16:39,200
Let's put on a tape.

342
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:41,560
It might help you unwind.

343
00:16:43,960 --> 00:16:44,800
Look.

344
00:16:45,080 --> 00:16:46,240
This one is huge right now.

345
00:16:46,560 --> 00:16:47,800
The Price of Madness.

346
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:49,440
I want to see

347
00:16:49,600 --> 00:16:50,440
how wild it gets.

348
00:16:51,140 --> 00:16:52,000
You sit over there.

349
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:52,920
I'll set it up for us.

350
00:16:52,920 --> 00:16:53,960
Don't worry about it.

351
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:54,800
Sit, sit.

352
00:16:56,920 --> 00:16:58,920
Why keep reading that script?

353
00:16:59,360 --> 00:17:01,360
It's a crime drama.

354
00:17:01,360 --> 00:17:03,160
Just relax a little.

355
00:17:03,680 --> 00:17:04,960
Come on, watch.

356
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:06,280
I'll get it going.

357
00:17:06,280 --> 00:17:09,240
Let's see how wild it really is.

358
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:10,080
Here we go.

359
00:17:12,360 --> 00:17:13,200
It's started.

360
00:17:14,840 --> 00:17:15,680
Look.

361
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:17,120
See? Trouble right off the bat.

362
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:18,640
A chase scene.

363
00:17:20,720 --> 00:17:21,560
That's not right.

364
00:17:22,750 --> 00:17:23,770
This isn't the beginning.

365
00:17:24,720 --> 00:17:25,760
Let me fix it for us.

366
00:17:25,760 --> 00:17:26,800
Hold on. I need to rewind.

367
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:28,200
I'll rewind it.

368
00:17:28,920 --> 00:17:31,040
Starting off this wild?

369
00:17:31,040 --> 00:17:32,520
Okay, play.

370
00:17:36,840 --> 00:17:37,880
Wait. What is this?

371
00:17:41,840 --> 00:17:42,880
What is this?

372
00:17:44,360 --> 00:17:45,640
Why are you showing me this?

373
00:17:45,640 --> 00:17:47,280
No, I didn't mean to show you this.

374
00:17:47,280 --> 00:17:48,880
My guy gave it to me.

375
00:17:49,380 --> 00:17:50,240
No, Qin'e.

376
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:51,440
I asked my guy to get it.

377
00:17:51,440 --> 00:17:52,440
My guy picked it up.

378
00:17:52,440 --> 00:17:53,440
It won't turn off.

379
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:55,760
Get your stuff out.

380
00:17:57,640 --> 00:17:59,280
I'm going, I'm going.

381
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:00,120
No, this...

382
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:01,840
I borrowed this lousy thing from him.

383
00:18:01,840 --> 00:18:03,110
What's he doing?

384
00:18:03,120 --> 00:18:04,250
Trying to get me in trouble?

385
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:05,560
Your coat.

386
00:18:07,760 --> 00:18:08,680
There's too much stuff.

387
00:18:10,840 --> 00:18:11,880
There, there.

388
00:18:13,120 --> 00:18:15,120
So much stuff.

389
00:18:17,760 --> 00:18:19,360
See? No problem.

390
00:18:24,680 --> 00:18:26,680
Look, look.

391
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:29,560
You're so cute when you smile.

392
00:18:30,040 --> 00:18:31,400
You should smile more often.

393
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:32,760
Got it?

394
00:18:32,840 --> 00:18:35,640
Don't keep life so tense.

395
00:18:37,280 --> 00:18:38,120
If you ask me,

396
00:18:38,760 --> 00:18:40,280
you play a female general onstage.

397
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:41,920
But offstage,

398
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:44,880
smile more.

399
00:18:45,520 --> 00:18:46,360
You're really cute.

400
00:19:05,960 --> 00:19:07,000
I think you're beautiful.

401
00:19:10,330 --> 00:19:11,450
To me, you're the prettiest.

402
00:21:35,840 --> 00:21:42,800
♪Pick up the saucer in your hands
and start playing♪

403
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:49,400
♪The tune is easy,
but the words are hard to say♪

404
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:55,960
♪Each line can't sing all life's pain♪

405
00:21:55,960 --> 00:22:02,360
♪Gentlemen and officers,
listen with pleasure♪

406
00:22:13,680 --> 00:22:14,880
What are you doing here?

407
00:22:14,880 --> 00:22:15,900
- Sanyuan.
- Sanyuan.

408
00:22:15,900 --> 00:22:16,740
Something's wrong.

409
00:22:16,740 --> 00:22:17,600
What?

410
00:22:17,600 --> 00:22:18,680
Shunzi got hurt.

411
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:19,720
He's getting bandaged.

412
00:22:19,820 --> 00:22:20,680
What happened?

413
00:22:20,680 --> 00:22:21,520
Take a look.

414
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:29,840
Who did this? How did it get so bad?

415
00:22:30,180 --> 00:22:31,040
What?

416
00:22:31,040 --> 00:22:31,960
My mom did it.

417
00:22:32,400 --> 00:22:33,280
Your mom did this?

418
00:22:33,600 --> 00:22:34,440
This...

419
00:22:34,520 --> 00:22:35,600
This is Shunzi's kid.

420
00:22:36,520 --> 00:22:37,640
Shunzi's daughter.

421
00:22:38,330 --> 00:22:39,680
What's your name? How old are you?

422
00:22:39,960 --> 00:22:42,240
I'm Juhua. I'm six.

423
00:22:43,560 --> 00:22:44,400
What happened?

424
00:22:45,040 --> 00:22:46,610
His wife ran off with someone.

425
00:22:46,610 --> 00:22:47,510
Leaving is one thing.

426
00:22:47,510 --> 00:22:49,040
But look what they did to Shunzi.

427
00:22:50,840 --> 00:22:51,840
He's badly hurt.

428
00:22:52,160 --> 00:22:53,000
Call the police.

429
00:22:53,520 --> 00:22:54,840
Shunzi won't let us.

430
00:22:55,240 --> 00:22:57,680
He says she's still Juhua's mom.

431
00:22:58,020 --> 00:22:58,880
Come on, come on.

432
00:22:58,880 --> 00:22:59,920
Easy, easy.

433
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:01,270
- Bro.
- Here, hold him up.

434
00:23:01,270 --> 00:23:02,400
Careful. Easy, easy.

435
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:03,510
Come on, quick.

436
00:23:03,510 --> 00:23:04,380
Easy, easy.

437
00:23:04,380 --> 00:23:05,600
- Hold him.
- Watch out.

438
00:23:06,260 --> 00:23:07,120
Come on, sit.

439
00:23:07,120 --> 00:23:07,960
Dr. Du.

440
00:23:08,040 --> 00:23:09,880
You're getting good at bandaging.

441
00:23:10,520 --> 00:23:12,080
Can he even eat now?

442
00:23:13,160 --> 00:23:14,240
Why can't he?

443
00:23:14,240 --> 00:23:15,360
I left his mouth clear.

444
00:23:16,920 --> 00:23:18,960
Dad, how did you end up like this?

445
00:23:19,520 --> 00:23:20,760
I'm okay.

446
00:23:21,320 --> 00:23:22,160
I'm fine.

447
00:23:24,080 --> 00:23:25,360
I'm just not capable enough.

448
00:23:26,560 --> 00:23:27,520
I made my kid suffer.

449
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:30,560
What suffering? It's nothing.

450
00:23:31,080 --> 00:23:32,720
We can't let a minor setback

451
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:34,920
make us deny our whole life, right?

452
00:23:35,720 --> 00:23:38,280
Of course, this isn't exactly minor.

453
00:23:39,520 --> 00:23:40,760
I'm just not good enough.

454
00:23:42,560 --> 00:23:44,600
She wants a better life.

455
00:23:45,120 --> 00:23:46,200
How can I stop her?

456
00:23:47,360 --> 00:23:48,880
We stagehands

457
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:50,920
are lowlife.

458
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:52,800
Don't say that in front of the kid.

459
00:23:53,440 --> 00:23:55,720
No one's better or worse.
It's up to you.

460
00:23:55,720 --> 00:23:56,560
Dad.

461
00:23:57,040 --> 00:23:57,880
Then,

462
00:23:58,240 --> 00:24:01,000
I'm singing
at the Children's Palace tomorrow.

463
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:02,240
Can you still take me?

464
00:24:02,840 --> 00:24:04,200
I can't go.

465
00:24:04,960 --> 00:24:05,800
Tomorrow,

466
00:24:06,520 --> 00:24:08,080
have Uncle Sparrow take you.

467
00:24:08,760 --> 00:24:09,600
Shunzi,

468
00:24:09,960 --> 00:24:10,800
tomorrow,

469
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:12,240
I've got a stage setup job.

470
00:24:12,240 --> 00:24:14,080
I can't get away.

471
00:24:14,080 --> 00:24:14,920
Right.

472
00:24:16,460 --> 00:24:17,320
Well.

473
00:24:17,320 --> 00:24:18,160
Don't worry.

474
00:24:18,840 --> 00:24:20,160
Listen. I'll take the kid.

475
00:24:20,720 --> 00:24:21,920
Just tell me where to go.

476
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:23,840
(Singing Match)
Here.

477
00:24:23,840 --> 00:24:24,720
(Qinchuan Qualifier)

478
00:24:24,720 --> 00:24:26,320
(Registration Desk)
Diao Juhua, right?

479
00:24:26,320 --> 00:24:27,180
Yes. How much?

480
00:24:27,180 --> 00:24:28,060
Eighty.

481
00:24:28,560 --> 00:24:30,280
Why is this contest so pricey?

482
00:24:30,800 --> 00:24:32,200
Children are tomorrow's sun.

483
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:33,640
They're the next generation.

484
00:24:33,640 --> 00:24:35,560
It's not pricey to invest in the future.

485
00:24:36,340 --> 00:24:37,200
Come on.

486
00:24:37,200 --> 00:24:38,080
Fine, I'll invest.

487
00:24:39,680 --> 00:24:40,600
Here, Juhua. Hold this.

488
00:24:40,600 --> 00:24:41,990
- This is five.
- Forty-five.

489
00:24:41,990 --> 00:24:43,160
And this is ten.

490
00:24:43,160 --> 00:24:44,080
Put it on.

491
00:24:48,140 --> 00:24:54,220
(Little Bud Cup Singing Match)

492
00:25:19,160 --> 00:25:20,000
You look great.

493
00:25:20,160 --> 00:25:22,000
Remember what I taught you?

494
00:25:23,120 --> 00:25:24,760
Don't get nervous in there.

495
00:25:24,760 --> 00:25:26,400
Sing it just like I taught you, okay?

496
00:25:30,080 --> 00:25:31,920
What's your name? How old are you?

497
00:25:31,920 --> 00:25:32,910
What song will you sing?

498
00:25:39,880 --> 00:25:41,640
So, what's your name?

499
00:25:41,960 --> 00:25:42,800
Juhua.

500
00:25:43,680 --> 00:25:44,880
I mean your full name.

501
00:25:45,760 --> 00:25:46,840
Diao Juhua.

502
00:25:47,080 --> 00:25:48,880
What song will you sing today?

503
00:25:49,520 --> 00:25:50,640
Do you have backing music?

504
00:25:52,760 --> 00:25:53,600
Hey, kiddo.

505
00:25:53,920 --> 00:25:54,960
I'm Juhua.

506
00:25:55,680 --> 00:25:57,320
Juhua, let me explain.

507
00:25:57,320 --> 00:25:58,320
For kids singing here,

508
00:25:58,320 --> 00:25:59,560
there's a time limit.

509
00:25:59,760 --> 00:26:02,120
If you don't speak or sing,

510
00:26:02,120 --> 00:26:03,000
once time is up,

511
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:04,160
you'll lose your chance.

512
00:26:09,440 --> 00:26:10,320
Not this one.

513
00:26:11,040 --> 00:26:12,320
Miss, please take her off.

514
00:26:12,320 --> 00:26:13,290
Let's have the next one.

515
00:26:13,480 --> 00:26:14,320
Okay.

516
00:26:14,760 --> 00:26:15,700
♪Once outside♪

517
00:26:15,700 --> 00:26:19,480
(Little Bud Cup Singing Match)
♪My back feels behind♪

518
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:22,220
(Qinchuan Qualifier)
♪So I can keep my belly♪

519
00:26:22,220 --> 00:26:24,480
♪Out front♪

520
00:26:24,960 --> 00:26:29,600
♪All uncles are uncles♪

521
00:26:30,040 --> 00:26:34,880
♪Tables and stools are all wood♪

522
00:26:34,880 --> 00:26:39,040
♪One step forward and one step back
means nothing♪

523
00:26:39,720 --> 00:26:44,000
♪Donkeys and oxen are beasts♪

524
00:26:46,160 --> 00:26:48,240
Is Diao Juhua's guardian here?

525
00:26:48,840 --> 00:26:49,680
Yes.

526
00:26:53,840 --> 00:26:54,880
Sanyuan,

527
00:26:55,440 --> 00:26:57,040
I knew it was you.

528
00:26:57,760 --> 00:26:59,000
Long time no see.

529
00:27:00,040 --> 00:27:01,000
Mi Lan.

530
00:27:06,560 --> 00:27:08,520
You haven't changed a bit.

531
00:27:08,520 --> 00:27:09,440
Neither have you.

532
00:27:10,320 --> 00:27:11,400
You don't mean that.

533
00:27:11,400 --> 00:27:12,280
I do.

534
00:27:13,840 --> 00:27:15,240
Is Juhua your kid?

535
00:27:15,760 --> 00:27:16,680
No, she isn't.

536
00:27:16,680 --> 00:27:17,760
She's my buddy's kid.

537
00:27:17,960 --> 00:27:19,320
My buddy is sick.

538
00:27:19,320 --> 00:27:20,960
I brought the kid to the contest.

539
00:27:21,760 --> 00:27:23,240
She's got an off-key voice.

540
00:27:25,880 --> 00:27:27,640
That doesn't mean
she won't have a chance.

541
00:27:28,120 --> 00:27:29,040
Look at Laidi.

542
00:27:32,120 --> 00:27:34,280
This time, let's be honest.

543
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:36,880
Don't give her any special treatment.

544
00:27:37,440 --> 00:27:38,800
Just say it like it is.

545
00:27:39,280 --> 00:27:41,420
If she's not cut out, tell her straight.

546
00:27:41,430 --> 00:27:42,470
Better make it sound firm,

547
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:44,320
so she'll drop the idea for good.

548
00:27:45,600 --> 00:27:47,800
If she doesn't fit, don't let her do it.

549
00:27:47,800 --> 00:27:48,640
Got it?

550
00:27:49,720 --> 00:27:51,180
Don't worry so much about the result.

551
00:27:51,520 --> 00:27:52,960
Let her hang with us for a while.

552
00:27:52,960 --> 00:27:53,800
That'd be good too.

553
00:27:54,160 --> 00:27:56,200
Think of it
as helping your buddy babysit.

554
00:27:56,760 --> 00:27:58,360
Can you babysit her?

555
00:28:00,760 --> 00:28:03,400
Okay, then that's fine, right?

556
00:28:04,240 --> 00:28:05,880
Bro, why are you in Chang'an?

557
00:28:07,760 --> 00:28:09,280
Are Caixiang and Laidi here too?

558
00:28:09,640 --> 00:28:11,120
Yes, they're here.

559
00:28:12,360 --> 00:28:14,120
Can you take me to meet them?

560
00:28:15,120 --> 00:28:15,960
Of course.

561
00:28:17,280 --> 00:28:18,160
Of course, I can.

562
00:28:18,750 --> 00:28:19,660
(Mi Lan, Chairman)
No.

563
00:28:20,080 --> 00:28:20,920
Why?

564
00:28:22,120 --> 00:28:23,160
Why do you think?

565
00:28:29,640 --> 00:28:31,640
How is she now?

566
00:28:33,640 --> 00:28:34,560
Same as ever.

567
00:28:34,960 --> 00:28:36,560
I don't see much change.

568
00:28:37,160 --> 00:28:38,920
Her clothes look pricier now.

569
00:28:39,720 --> 00:28:41,800
Just like that title on her card.

570
00:28:45,280 --> 00:28:46,760
She is always smart.

571
00:28:47,800 --> 00:28:49,800
One right move led to another.

572
00:28:50,840 --> 00:28:52,800
I somehow think you should go.

573
00:28:53,840 --> 00:28:55,760
Maybe she can help you find a job.

574
00:28:56,520 --> 00:28:58,080
She knows the Children's Palace well.

575
00:28:58,480 --> 00:28:59,440
She's the boss there.

576
00:29:00,800 --> 00:29:01,640
No.

577
00:29:02,840 --> 00:29:04,360
All these years, I'm used to this.

578
00:29:05,400 --> 00:29:06,760
I think this is pretty good.

579
00:29:06,760 --> 00:29:07,720
No need to overthink it.

580
00:29:08,760 --> 00:29:10,160
I don't want to change anymore.

581
00:29:11,280 --> 00:29:12,600
Nor can I change much anyway.

582
00:29:21,160 --> 00:29:23,880
It's just dinner.
Why pick somewhere so fancy?

583
00:29:31,320 --> 00:29:32,240
Is this the place?

584
00:29:36,160 --> 00:29:37,000
Right here.

585
00:29:37,400 --> 00:29:38,240
Come on, hurry.

586
00:29:39,720 --> 00:29:40,560
Hey.

587
00:29:41,020 --> 00:29:41,880
Little Laidi.

588
00:29:41,880 --> 00:29:42,720
Mi Lan.

589
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:44,040
Look how grown up you are.

590
00:29:44,040 --> 00:29:45,600
- Long time no see.
- She's grown up.

591
00:29:45,600 --> 00:29:46,440
Yeah.

592
00:29:47,320 --> 00:29:48,760
Come on, have a seat.

593
00:29:48,760 --> 00:29:50,000
Caixiang didn't come?

594
00:29:50,520 --> 00:29:52,560
She's got something going on.

595
00:29:52,560 --> 00:29:53,960
She couldn't get away.

596
00:29:54,560 --> 00:29:55,680
Come sit down first.

597
00:29:57,720 --> 00:29:59,280
What's keeping Caixiang so busy?

598
00:30:00,080 --> 00:30:01,760
She's running a small business now.

599
00:30:02,360 --> 00:30:03,840
She can't leave her stall.

600
00:30:03,840 --> 00:30:05,320
- Thanks.
- What kind of business?

601
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:08,120
She sells liangpi

602
00:30:08,640 --> 00:30:09,880
at the Diaojia Village entrance.

603
00:30:13,760 --> 00:30:15,160
Laidi,

604
00:30:15,160 --> 00:30:16,960
you've really made something
of yourself.

605
00:30:16,960 --> 00:30:18,480
You're a big star now.

606
00:30:19,040 --> 00:30:20,280
You know,

607
00:30:20,280 --> 00:30:22,360
you're in the news nationwide.

608
00:30:22,720 --> 00:30:24,000
I'm truly happy for you.

609
00:30:24,480 --> 00:30:25,320
Mi Lan,

610
00:30:25,600 --> 00:30:27,400
back when I was inside,

611
00:30:27,400 --> 00:30:29,040
you took such good care of her.

612
00:30:30,880 --> 00:30:32,880
You should thank Mi Lan properly.

613
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:34,200
Thank you, Mi Lan.

614
00:30:34,440 --> 00:30:36,440
I'll never forget what you said to me

615
00:30:36,440 --> 00:30:37,640
before you left the troupe.

616
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:40,440
Honestly, I forgot what I said.

617
00:30:40,840 --> 00:30:43,160
I really didn't do much for the kid.

618
00:30:43,680 --> 00:30:45,240
But even back then, I knew

619
00:30:45,240 --> 00:30:47,680
that Yi Qing'e was bound to be a star.

620
00:30:48,280 --> 00:30:50,560
Hey, is everyone in the troupe okay?

621
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:51,840
They're doing great.

622
00:30:51,840 --> 00:30:53,880
Come back to the county when you can.

623
00:30:54,480 --> 00:30:56,240
If they saw you now,

624
00:30:56,640 --> 00:30:57,800
they'd all be blown away.

625
00:30:58,160 --> 00:30:59,280
No one would've imagined

626
00:31:00,400 --> 00:31:01,720
you'd become who you are today.

627
00:31:01,720 --> 00:31:02,560
Ma'am,

628
00:31:02,750 --> 00:31:03,720
you must've mixed it up.

629
00:31:03,720 --> 00:31:05,000
Why is there so much chili?

630
00:31:05,980 --> 00:31:06,840
I'm sorry.

631
00:31:06,840 --> 00:31:08,360
I'll make you a new one right away.

632
00:31:14,040 --> 00:31:15,400
Ma'am, one bowl of liangpi.

633
00:31:15,400 --> 00:31:16,880
Extra chili, no garlic.

634
00:31:24,720 --> 00:31:26,120
It looks like you're doing well.

635
00:31:26,480 --> 00:31:27,560
That sounded a little sour.

636
00:31:29,800 --> 00:31:31,400
My jealousy comes by the basin.

637
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:34,040
I really did miss you,

638
00:31:34,040 --> 00:31:35,080
so I came to check on you.

639
00:31:37,120 --> 00:31:38,160
Then sit over there.

640
00:31:38,160 --> 00:31:39,080
Watch closely in a bit.

641
00:31:39,080 --> 00:31:40,080
Sure, ma'am.

642
00:31:50,480 --> 00:31:51,600
Peel a couple of cucumbers.

643
00:31:52,360 --> 00:31:53,400
Or peel some garlic.

644
00:31:55,640 --> 00:31:57,160
How do you still have this stuff?

645
00:31:58,960 --> 00:32:01,200
This is how ordinary folks live.

646
00:32:03,320 --> 00:32:04,960
A simple life is better.

647
00:32:06,680 --> 00:32:08,440
Not like me, alone in Beijing.

648
00:32:08,440 --> 00:32:10,480
When I get home late to a cold kitchen.

649
00:32:11,280 --> 00:32:12,320
I don't even want to eat.

650
00:32:14,400 --> 00:32:15,240
Let me.

651
00:32:25,120 --> 00:32:26,040
What about your spouse?

652
00:32:27,880 --> 00:32:29,520
We've been apart for four years.

653
00:32:30,960 --> 00:32:32,640
If it weren't for this company,

654
00:32:33,520 --> 00:32:35,160
it'd be better to live apart at our age.

655
00:32:36,680 --> 00:32:38,360
I've actually figured it out.

656
00:32:38,560 --> 00:32:40,480
Marriage is just sharing a life.

657
00:32:41,480 --> 00:32:42,960
As long as no lines are crossed,

658
00:32:44,080 --> 00:32:45,600
the marriage can still hold together.

659
00:32:46,280 --> 00:32:47,640
Can't you look on the bright side?

660
00:32:51,080 --> 00:32:51,920
Do you have kids?

661
00:32:52,480 --> 00:32:53,320
No.

662
00:32:54,280 --> 00:32:55,400
Luckily, I don't.

663
00:32:56,960 --> 00:32:57,960
Once you have a kid,

664
00:32:57,960 --> 00:32:59,480
your mind is all on the child,

665
00:32:59,720 --> 00:33:01,400
and your career takes a back seat.

666
00:33:02,760 --> 00:33:04,360
Listen to that.

667
00:33:04,360 --> 00:33:06,120
I'm not sure who you're taking a jab at.

668
00:33:07,160 --> 00:33:08,000
I don't get it.

669
00:33:13,040 --> 00:33:14,200
You two are together now?

670
00:33:17,640 --> 00:33:18,680
He told you that?

671
00:33:20,000 --> 00:33:21,120
Does he need to?

672
00:33:21,600 --> 00:33:23,600
When Sanyuan mentions you,

673
00:33:23,600 --> 00:33:25,240
his eyes just light up,

674
00:33:25,880 --> 00:33:27,600
just like back in Ningzhou.

675
00:33:29,240 --> 00:33:30,720
I really envy you two.

676
00:33:31,000 --> 00:33:33,160
You can connect on a deeper level.

677
00:33:34,240 --> 00:33:35,320
Comforting me?

678
00:33:35,320 --> 00:33:36,680
Afraid I'd feel bad?

679
00:33:37,400 --> 00:33:38,240
No need.

680
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:40,960
Now, anyone who's not blind

681
00:33:40,960 --> 00:33:42,080
can tell at a glance

682
00:33:42,840 --> 00:33:44,000
which one of us

683
00:33:44,720 --> 00:33:45,760
is doing better.

684
00:33:48,440 --> 00:33:49,280
Sis,

685
00:33:49,720 --> 00:33:51,320
you're better than me at everything.

686
00:33:52,280 --> 00:33:53,520
You sing better than I.

687
00:33:53,520 --> 00:33:54,840
You've got a better character.

688
00:33:56,720 --> 00:33:58,360
Back then, if it had been you,

689
00:33:58,360 --> 00:33:59,880
you wouldn't have married someone

690
00:33:59,880 --> 00:34:01,320
nearly 20 years older

691
00:34:01,600 --> 00:34:03,320
without love.

692
00:34:04,200 --> 00:34:05,520
And now, if it were you,

693
00:34:05,840 --> 00:34:08,080
you'd divorce him in a heartbeat.

694
00:34:08,080 --> 00:34:10,200
You wouldn't still endure it like me.

695
00:34:14,120 --> 00:34:16,080
Only I know what I've been through

696
00:34:17,400 --> 00:34:18,640
all these years.

697
00:34:28,520 --> 00:34:29,480
It'll all pass.

698
00:34:31,960 --> 00:34:34,360
We're not in the County Troupe now,

699
00:34:34,680 --> 00:34:35,640
fighting over the lead,

700
00:34:35,640 --> 00:34:37,320
as if it were life or death.

701
00:34:38,160 --> 00:34:39,000
What's the point?

702
00:34:41,900 --> 00:34:42,760
Do you want liangpi?

703
00:34:42,760 --> 00:34:43,600
I'll mix you a bowl.

704
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:45,680
I'm really good at it now.

705
00:34:46,280 --> 00:34:47,240
That's all I can do now.

706
00:34:48,000 --> 00:34:49,080
All you can do?

707
00:34:49,200 --> 00:34:50,140
You don't sing anymore?

708
00:35:03,240 --> 00:35:10,240
♪Grandma tells of the brave old days♪

709
00:35:12,040 --> 00:35:19,560
♪When sacrifices were made♪

710
00:35:19,560 --> 00:35:21,320
Wow, you really sound worse now.

711
00:35:21,800 --> 00:35:22,840
I like it that way.

712
00:35:22,840 --> 00:35:25,120
Regardless, I still like singing.

713
00:35:25,120 --> 00:35:26,040
It makes me happy.

714
00:35:26,640 --> 00:35:28,200
If you're so good, you sing.

715
00:35:29,400 --> 00:35:30,240
Sing.

716
00:35:37,840 --> 00:35:42,720
♪Oh, Grandma♪

717
00:35:42,720 --> 00:35:49,720
♪17 years of care, deep as the ocean♪

718
00:36:14,480 --> 00:36:15,320
Qin'e,

719
00:36:16,640 --> 00:36:17,480
you're back.

720
00:36:19,040 --> 00:36:20,000
No, I...

721
00:36:22,840 --> 00:36:24,080
That's not what I meant.

722
00:36:24,720 --> 00:36:25,560
Last time,

723
00:36:25,800 --> 00:36:26,840
you got it wrong.

724
00:36:30,600 --> 00:36:31,440
Just let me explain.

725
00:36:32,120 --> 00:36:33,200
I really didn't...

726
00:36:34,480 --> 00:36:35,320
Qin'e.

727
00:36:37,240 --> 00:36:38,160
I'm sorry.

728
00:36:42,980 --> 00:36:43,840
No.

729
00:36:43,840 --> 00:36:45,040
Qin'e, you...

730
00:37:05,120 --> 00:37:06,400
This is my pledge letter.

731
00:37:07,040 --> 00:37:10,800
Never go against Yi Qin'e's wishes

732
00:37:10,800 --> 00:37:12,800
in anything I do.

733
00:37:14,200 --> 00:37:17,320
If Yi Qin'e says east,

734
00:37:18,040 --> 00:37:19,320
I will never go west.

735
00:37:20,680 --> 00:37:24,120
Devote my life to Yi Qin'e.

736
00:37:24,680 --> 00:37:27,080
Be her support off the field.

737
00:37:27,520 --> 00:37:30,680
Have warm salt water, throat lozenges,

738
00:37:30,680 --> 00:37:32,040
and a dry towel

739
00:37:32,040 --> 00:37:33,080
ready in advance.

740
00:37:34,280 --> 00:37:36,280
Make sure that after the show,

741
00:37:36,280 --> 00:37:38,680
her coat is brought right away,

742
00:37:38,680 --> 00:37:39,840
so she doesn't catch a cold.

743
00:37:41,880 --> 00:37:45,800
Respect Yi Qin'e's artistic exchanges.

744
00:37:45,800 --> 00:37:47,960
No suspicion. No interference.

745
00:37:48,560 --> 00:37:52,360
If any rumors about Yi Qin'e

746
00:37:52,360 --> 00:37:54,640
come up out there,

747
00:37:55,200 --> 00:37:58,440
I must step up at once.

748
00:37:59,280 --> 00:38:03,280
That is my pledge to Yi Qin'e.

749
00:38:04,040 --> 00:38:05,480
The final say

750
00:38:05,480 --> 00:38:08,080
belongs solely to Yi Qin'e.

751
00:38:09,480 --> 00:38:10,320
Qin'e,

752
00:38:11,280 --> 00:38:12,840
I lost my head last time.

753
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:16,480
I apologize.

754
00:38:18,040 --> 00:38:19,280
I won't do that again.

755
00:38:21,080 --> 00:38:21,920
Okay?

756
00:38:22,760 --> 00:38:24,040
You did nothing wrong.

757
00:38:24,880 --> 00:38:26,280
It's on me.

758
00:38:28,960 --> 00:38:29,880
You should go.

759
00:38:33,640 --> 00:38:34,560
Don't come back

760
00:38:38,160 --> 00:38:39,400
anymore.

761
00:38:42,560 --> 00:38:44,000
There's no chance for us.

762
00:38:47,680 --> 00:38:49,280
Is it because of that rumor?

763
00:38:51,760 --> 00:38:52,640
Don't worry.

764
00:38:53,280 --> 00:38:54,640
I'll get you an answer.

765
00:39:30,660 --> 00:39:32,980
(Zhijiu Bookstore)

766
00:39:43,760 --> 00:39:44,960
Pick any book you want.

767
00:39:58,800 --> 00:40:00,080
Scholar of Tangcheng.

768
00:40:02,300 --> 00:40:03,160
Who are you?

769
00:40:03,160 --> 00:40:04,250
How do you know my pen name?

770
00:40:04,680 --> 00:40:05,770
Did you write

771
00:40:05,790 --> 00:40:06,910
The Pan Jinlian in Chang'an?

772
00:40:07,360 --> 00:40:08,720
Yeah, I wrote it. So what?

773
00:40:18,200 --> 00:40:18,940
I'm sorry. Sorry.

774
00:40:18,950 --> 00:40:19,960
Who told you to write it?

775
00:40:19,960 --> 00:40:21,260
I didn't write it.

776
00:40:21,270 --> 00:40:22,410
Her coworker put me up to it.

777
00:40:22,420 --> 00:40:23,280
That's why I wrote it.

778
00:40:23,280 --> 00:40:24,120
Who is it?

779
00:40:24,280 --> 00:40:25,400
Her coworker.

780
00:40:25,400 --> 00:40:26,520
She stayed anonymous.

781
00:40:47,840 --> 00:40:48,680
Zhou Yuzhi.

782
00:40:49,120 --> 00:40:50,320
Jiahe, what brings you here?

783
00:40:50,840 --> 00:40:52,240
I came to see how you're doing.

784
00:40:52,240 --> 00:40:53,750
You've been off so long. Are you okay?

785
00:40:53,750 --> 00:40:55,440
I'm fine, just taking it slow.

786
00:40:55,800 --> 00:40:58,120
The doctor says coughs linger.

787
00:40:58,600 --> 00:40:59,440
I made some porridge.

788
00:40:59,440 --> 00:41:00,480
Have some with me later.

789
00:41:00,480 --> 00:41:01,320
Sure.

790
00:41:01,560 --> 00:41:03,200
Why bring so much stuff?

791
00:41:03,400 --> 00:41:04,960
My mom gave it to me. It's too much.

792
00:41:04,960 --> 00:41:06,040
So, I brought some for you.

793
00:41:06,040 --> 00:41:06,880
Okay.

794
00:41:08,240 --> 00:41:10,000
When are you doing Yang Pai Feng?

795
00:41:10,520 --> 00:41:11,840
They haven't set a date yet.

796
00:41:12,480 --> 00:41:13,440
Why?

797
00:41:14,160 --> 00:41:15,120
What's the point?

798
00:41:16,600 --> 00:41:18,720
If my transfer had gone through,

799
00:41:18,720 --> 00:41:19,960
I wouldn't be here singing.

800
00:41:20,840 --> 00:41:21,840
I'm so mad.

801
00:41:22,320 --> 00:41:23,680
It wasted my best years.

802
00:41:23,680 --> 00:41:24,800
All year long,

803
00:41:24,800 --> 00:41:26,600
I dated three or four men,

804
00:41:26,610 --> 00:41:27,720
but none of them worked out.

805
00:41:27,720 --> 00:41:29,720
I swapped your pillow for down.

806
00:41:29,720 --> 00:41:31,240
(The Choice)
Better than buckwheat.

807
00:41:31,240 --> 00:41:32,080
Sure.

808
00:41:34,100 --> 00:41:38,220
(Scholar of Tangcheng, Lead Writer)

809
00:41:42,560 --> 00:41:43,760
Jiahe, don't move.

810
00:41:51,160 --> 00:41:52,520
What magazine is this?

811
00:41:54,120 --> 00:41:55,480
Is this Tangcheng Tales?

812
00:41:56,520 --> 00:41:57,440
Where are the cover

813
00:41:57,440 --> 00:41:58,880
and missing pages of this book?

814
00:42:00,440 --> 00:42:02,120
Did you pin them on the notice board?

815
00:42:03,520 --> 00:42:04,360
Answer me.

816
00:42:08,480 --> 00:42:09,360
Yes.

817
00:42:10,200 --> 00:42:11,480
Why would you do that?

818
00:42:12,280 --> 00:42:14,160
I've always looked out for her.

819
00:42:14,960 --> 00:42:16,240
But I only asked her once

820
00:42:16,240 --> 00:42:17,960
to let me play the second female lead.

821
00:42:17,960 --> 00:42:19,440
She gave me the official runaround.

822
00:42:20,440 --> 00:42:21,720
In that moment,

823
00:42:22,800 --> 00:42:24,320
I felt she deserved no pity.

824
00:42:26,600 --> 00:42:28,000
You're not as good onstage,

825
00:42:28,000 --> 00:42:29,600
so you pull these shady moves.

826
00:42:30,040 --> 00:42:31,240
I really misjudged you.

827
00:42:31,640 --> 00:42:33,480
No, Jiahe, you...

828
00:42:33,480 --> 00:42:34,320
Let go.

829
00:42:35,440 --> 00:42:36,680
Chu Jiahe,

830
00:42:37,760 --> 00:42:39,680
this isn't Ningzhou anymore.

831
00:42:40,560 --> 00:42:42,360
You're not the lead anymore.

832
00:42:43,320 --> 00:42:44,440
Do you know how you got

833
00:42:44,440 --> 00:42:45,600
your Yang Pai Feng?

834
00:42:47,040 --> 00:42:48,520
She had no time to perform it,

835
00:42:49,320 --> 00:42:50,480
so it was handed to you.

836
00:42:51,280 --> 00:42:52,600
I heard it myself.

837
00:42:53,840 --> 00:42:55,080
She told Troupe Leader Shan.

838
00:42:56,960 --> 00:42:59,240
Or could you ever play the lead?

839
00:43:05,020 --> 00:43:06,940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

840
00:43:08,800 --> 00:43:10,800
For the lead in the troupe,

841
00:43:10,800 --> 00:43:13,400
strange things often happen.

842
00:43:13,400 --> 00:43:15,040
Do you have any ideas?

843
00:43:15,040 --> 00:43:16,480
There's nothing going on

844
00:43:16,480 --> 00:43:17,720
between Yi Qin'e and me.

845
00:43:17,720 --> 00:43:18,870
We're innocent.

846
00:43:18,910 --> 00:43:19,950
You know the answer.

847
00:43:20,020 --> 00:43:21,080
You started that rumor.

848
00:43:21,080 --> 00:43:22,280
I don't need your pity.

849
00:43:22,320 --> 00:43:23,650
I'd rather quit Yang Pai Feng

850
00:43:23,660 --> 00:43:24,920
than accept your charity.

851
00:43:25,214 --> 00:43:26,221
If you hadn't come to me,

852
00:43:26,232 --> 00:43:27,520
I would've come for you.

853
00:43:27,830 --> 00:43:29,800
Yi Qin'e, hurry and answer it!

854
00:43:29,800 --> 00:43:31,080
What happened to Liu Hongbing?

855
00:43:31,080 --> 00:43:32,680
He jumped off a building for you.

856
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,620
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

857
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:47,930
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

858
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,560
♪We met and brushed past♪

859
00:43:55,120 --> 00:44:02,420
♪Your shadow drifted out of sight♪

860
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:20,540
♪The stove fire blazed in my dream♪

861
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:27,710
♪Lit up the tracks of pearly tears♪

862
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:32,890
♪In my dream, water sleeves flew♪

863
00:44:34,020 --> 00:44:39,610
♪Hiding a lifetime of love♪

864
00:44:40,770 --> 00:44:44,970
♪The Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage♪

865
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:51,640
♪Spring water brewed strong wine♪

866
00:44:52,810 --> 00:44:57,500
♪Sheep moved through the valley♪

867
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:03,350
♪It felt like a promise
from another life♪

868
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:09,050
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

869
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:15,510
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

870
00:45:15,890 --> 00:45:21,170
♪If I chose again, I'd still roam♪

871
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:27,930
♪All over this sunlit plateau♪

872
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:33,350
♪The dream ends; the curtain falls♪

873
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:39,410
♪Moonlight washes off this stage makeup♪

874
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,920
♪The one in the mirror wears gray hair♪

875
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:51,220
♪Already sang all my joy and sorrow♪

876
00:45:52,020 --> 00:46:01,050
♪Already shouted across Qinchuan Plain♪
